<TITLE> BDR-BSF border conference starts Sunday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 11 (bdnews24.com)-A four-day Indo-Bangladesh border conference begins on Sunday at the Bangladesh Rifles's Peelkhana headquarters in Dhaka. The 24-member Bangladesh side will be represented by BDR director general Maj Gen Mainul Islam while the Indian Border Security Force delegation will be led by its director general ML Kumawat. The 18-member Indian team arrived in Dhaka on Saturday. A statement by BDR said signing of the joint records of discussion (JRD) would take place at the BDR headquarters on July 14. b
